01/04/2009
TIRANA, Albania -- Albania begins implementing its Stabilisation and Association Agreement (SAA) with the EU on Wednesday (April 1st), opening a new stage in its EU accession process. Minister of Integration Majlinda Bregu explained that effective Wednesday, the country will benefit from the right to free movement of goods and workers who have legal employment in the EU, thus having the same access as citizens of EU countries. (Balkan Web, Shekulli, Top News, Telegrafi - 31/03/09)
